</p></li><li id="LI_14F2360B54394026972652B71009438A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the ink system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="02DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C874C66-3A17-4AC4-886B-753A1A37D196.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>02 Open the ink system</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_FD655A5E8004471AA1088723A7B338FC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the APSU unit on the ink supply unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If you remove or disconnect the air tube of the APSU: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Close the air tubes of the printheads with the 8 white clamps. 
</p><note id="GUID-129E4591-8116-4052-A9F0-CCD1A5362B6C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The printheads will leak if the air tubes of the prinheads are not closed. 
</p></note></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_5232B115C44C4A13A0F0FA8D704DDD74" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_9BF138AF80F34359907B618BBA28D88F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-6BF0824B-5CE1-4498-B48F-0F80E9F710BB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1782B251-5DA2-42C9-8543-5FD100130AF2-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1782B251-5DA2-42C9-8543-5FD100130AF2-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-723730AC-2B9F-4818-9B0F-5DAC77C34DA8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BABC1033-0838-44CA-A31D-CD723D6A2AB6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BABC1033-0838-44CA-A31D-CD723D6A2AB6-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_1947AC2E2CFB464A9A7C88AD1C6DF2EE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_D43A91B2C36E4875B43F2DE0CE49C588" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1a 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Move the APSU 
</p><ul id="UL_1CB3F87A4C1F496B8A77C84D862B2E4C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_2C406BA20F2F4F5DBA85DFCAE34A6129" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the 2 connectors of the APSU. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Unhook the cable clip. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7EEA65BC-A110-42EB-97BA-DAA35C86FA26" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C191067-FC03-4325-BD77-C8C0855E42BB-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C191067-FC03-4325-BD77-C8C0855E42BB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1b 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 2 screws (Left side of the APSU). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the APSU from the slotted holes. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-898F0B6A-C980-4BAC-82AA-146C2070927B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-17F10DAE-D7F8-4600-863C-01D78F28ABCA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-17F10DAE-D7F8-4600-863C-01D78F28ABCA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1c 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the APSU on the Ink Compartment in the slotted holes. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7C473155-AE8A-4C52-A3AB-08D741CFE0E5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5A924F8A-B034-4982-9D82-9D4C14EE5709-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5A924F8A-B034-4982-9D82-9D4C14EE5709-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-8BA8F0A8-4979-4C5D-A487-4B34E5B4A24E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4E0D1F2E-D3AD-407E-B433-A2A179F2F2CC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4E0D1F2E-D3AD-407E-B433-A2A179F2F2CC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connectors. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Unhook the cable harness. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-13F3F3DC-3B34-4582-93AE-B95C3559ABB7" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Note the location of the red and blue RJ45 connectors 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-22D68F55-8BE0-4F10-B547-C49B3C96CFB9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F9336707-857D-47CD-A10E-BA5F4190169F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F9336707-857D-47CD-A10E-BA5F4190169F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Move the cable harness aside. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the screws of the PBA. 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-6DEF768F-E637-4061-ADAB-6D95DE4C7BE2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-566A636B-92B5-4C77-BCAB-2EBACA861F4A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-566A636B-92B5-4C77-BCAB-2EBACA861F4A-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-45C7C8C2-C7DA-4D93-828D-12DD66170BE8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DBD16D62-0B64-4AC4-8855-CE9A315E8312-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DBD16D62-0B64-4AC4-8855-CE9A315E8312-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the PBA 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7AA09193-8E8E-420E-8EC7-F97B6E5C9C69" class="- topic/note "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lift PBA at the right side. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide the PBA to the left. 
</p></li></ol></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C6C9EDCE-C783-42EE-853B-DDC70C0C1AB6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F838290C-CD3A-444C-B56A-39C8D6EA0F7F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F838290C-CD3A-444C-B56A-39C8D6EA0F7F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_97BC00975228435B8A284A8C547372BA" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-A35654C5-197F-4275-A958-9BAEACB836B1" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This connector is only used when the Jumbo roll is installed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Connector 12X110 is only used when the Jumbo roll is installed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Do not connect to Distribution PBA (22PBA02). 
</p><fig id="GUID-59E958A3-9C8D-4302-91ED-73CCE86A1D51" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6A0AEF42-55D2-4D11-8E9C-FD5BB196D7C4-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6A0AEF42-55D2-4D11-8E9C-FD5BB196D7C4-low.png"/></fig></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the service jumper,exit SDS and press "Restart"on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-6C63EF43-7F31-48D5-A8F0-5338D21560E2.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
